diagnosis.diagnostic_reasoning: Ms. ___ presented with symptoms including sharp right lower quadrant (RLQ) pain, nausea, and anorexia, which progressed to persistent localized RLQ pain. Physical examination revealed focal tenderness in the RLQ without rebound tenderness or guarding, supporting the diagnosis of acute appendicitis. Diarrhea and urinary frequency were noted but are not typical symptoms of appendicitis.
